    },
    {
      "text": "Nakajima Satoru Kanshū F1 Grand Prix (中嶋悟監修 Ｆ１ ＧＲＡＮＤ ＰＲＩＸ; \"Supervisor Satoru Nakajima F1 Grand Prix\") is a 1991 Sega Mega Drive Formula One video game based on the career of Satoru Nakajima, who was the first full-time Japanese racer in the history of Formula One. This is the third video game collaboration between Nakajima and Varie, following Nakajima Satoru F-1 Hero and Nakajima Satoru F-1 Hero 2 for the Famicom. The entire 1991 Formula One season can be re-enacted with any of the notable contenders from the prestigious Formula One racing organization.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    },
